From: Ghaf contributors <ghaf@tii.ae>
Subject: [PATCH] kms: composite the cursor on NVIDIA

The Tegra nvdisplay DRM driver accepts atomic updates for its cursor plane and
reports the updated coordinates in debugfs, but the scanned-out cursor remains
at the top-left corner. Disable the NVIDIA cursor plane so cosmic-comp renders
the cursor into the primary plane instead.
---
--- a/src/backend/kms/mod.rs
+++ b/src/backend/kms/mod.rs
@@ -937,6 +937,7 @@
                                 .contains("nvidia")
                         }) {
                             planes.overlay = vec![];
+                            planes.cursor = vec![];
                         }
                         // QUIRK: Cursor planes on evdi sometimes don't disappear correctly.
                         // TODO: Debug and figure out, as they can be a nice improvement.
